Assuming the slug is for a category you can do this:
```
from django.shortcuts import get_object_or_404


class ProductCategoryListView(ListView):
    template_name = &#39;products/product_list.html&#39;

    def get_queryset(request, *args, **kwargs):
        category = get_object_or_404(Category, slug=self.slug)
        products = Product.objects.filter(category=category)
        return products
```

In your ``Product`` model you can set a ``related_name`` in the category field, so it&#39;s easier to access the products from the category:

```
class Product(models.Model):
