This can be done using Aggregation Pipeline. 

Pipeline stages used are [$addFields][1], [$project][2] and [$replaceRoot][3]

Below is the Query used to get the result

     db.a.aggregate([
      {
        $addFields: {
          arr: [
            {
              k: &quot;$key&quot;,
              v: &quot;$value&quot;
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        $project: {
          _id: 1,
          newAttrs: {
            $arrayToObject: {
              $map: {
                input: &quot;$arr&quot;,
                as: &quot;pair&quot;,
                in: [
                  &quot;$$pair.k&quot;,
                  &quot;$$pair.v&quot;
                ]
              }
            }
          }
        }
      },
      {
        $replaceRoot: {
          newRoot: {
            $mergeObjects: [
              {
                _id: &quot;$_id&quot;
              },
              &quot;$newAttrs&quot;
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    ]);

Sample Data used:

    {&quot;_id&quot;:1,&quot;key&quot;:&quot;some_key&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:&quot;some_value&quot;}
    {&quot;_id&quot;:2,&quot;key&quot;:&quot;my_key&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:&quot;my_value&quot;}
    {&quot;_id&quot;:3,&quot;key&quot;:&quot;test_key&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:&quot;test_value&quot;}
    {&quot;_id&quot;:4,&quot;key&quot;:&quot;new_key&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:&quot;new_value&quot;}

Result obtained:

    {&quot;_id&quot;:1,&quot;some_key&quot;:&quot;some_value&quot;}
    {&quot;_id&quot;:2,&quot;my_key&quot;:&quot;my_value&quot;}
    {&quot;_id&quot;:3,&quot;test_key&quot;:&quot;test_value&quot;}
    {&quot;_id&quot;:4,&quot;new_key&quot;:&quot;new_value&quot;}

The 


  [1]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/addFields/
  [2]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/project/
  [3]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/replaceRoot/

