&lt;!-- language-all: lang-bat --&gt;Here&#39;s an example showing some redirects via a registry change. Please add to, or remove from it as required, but note that this is completely untested, so back up the User Shell Folders keys before trying it:
```
@Echo Off
Set &quot;3DOBJ=D:\%%USERNAME%%\3D Objects&quot;
Set &quot;CONT=D:\%%USERNAME%%\Contacts&quot;
Set &quot;DESK=D:\%%USERNAME%%\Desktop&quot;
Set &quot;DOCS=D:\%%USERNAME%%\Documents&quot;
Set &quot;DLOAD=D:\%%USERNAME%%\Downloads&quot;
Set &quot;FAVS=D:\%%USERNAME%%\Favorites&quot;
Set &quot;LINKS=D:\%%USERNAME%%\Links&quot;
Set &quot;MUSIC=D:\%%USERNAME%%\Music&quot;
Set &quot;PICS=D:\%%USERNAME%%\Pictures&quot;
Set &quot;GAMES=D:\%%USERNAME%%\Saved Games&quot;
Set &quot;SRCH=D:\%%USERNAME%%\Searches&quot;
Set &quot;VIDS=D:\%%USERNAME%%\Videos&quot;

Set &quot;USF=HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\User Shell Folders&quot;
(
	Reg Add &quot;%USF%&quot; /V &quot;{31C0DD25-9439-4F12-BF41-7FF4EDA38722}&quot; /T REG_EXPAND_SZ /D &quot;%3DOBJ%&quot; /F
	Reg Add &quot;%USF%&quot; /V &quot;{56784854-C6CB-462B-8169-88E350ACB882}&quot; /T REG_EXPAND_SZ /D &quot;%CONT%&quot; /F
	Reg Add &quot;%USF%&quot; /V &quot;Desktop&quot; /T REG_EXPAND_SZ /D &quot;%DESK%&quot; /F
	Reg Add &quot;%USF%&quot; /V &quot;Personal&quot; /T REG_EXPAND_SZ /D &quot;%DOCS%&quot; /F
	Reg Add &quot;%USF%&quot; /V &quot;{374DE290-123F-4565-9164-39C4925E467B}&quot; /T REG_EXPAND_SZ /D &quot;%DLOAD%&quot; /F
	Reg Add &quot;%USF%&quot; /V &quot;Favorites&quot; /T REG_EXPAND_SZ /D &quot;%FAVS%&quot; /F
	Reg Add &quot;%USF%&quot; /V &quot;{BFB9D5E0-C6A9-404C-B2B2-AE6DB6AF4968}&quot; /T REG_EXPAND_SZ /D &quot;%LINKS%&quot; /F
	Reg Add &quot;%USF%&quot; /V &quot;My Music&quot; /T REG_EXPAND_SZ /D &quot;%MUSIC%&quot; /F
	Reg Add &quot;%USF%&quot; /V &quot;My Pictures&quot; /T REG_EXPAND_SZ /D &quot;%PICS%&quot; /F
	Reg Add &quot;%USF%&quot; /V &quot;{4C5C32FF-BB9D-43B0-B5B4-2D72E54EAAA4}&quot; /T REG_EXPAND_SZ /D &quot;%GAMES%&quot; /F
	Reg Add &quot;%USF%&quot; /V &quot;{7D1D3A04-DEBB-4115-95CF-2F29DA2920DA}&quot; /T REG_EXPAND_SZ /D &quot;%SRCH%&quot; /F
	Reg Add &quot;%USF%&quot; /V &quot;My Video&quot; /T REG_EXPAND_SZ /D &quot;%VIDS%&quot; /F
)&gt;NUL

Shutdown /R /D P:2:4
```
Before using this you may wish need to modify the paths between the  **`=`** and closing **`&quot;`**, on lines `2` - `14` for those you&#39;d like as your new destinations. I have included `%%USERNAME%%` in those example paths because I prefer that the user&#39;s name is included, *especially if several profiles are redirected*. You&#39;ll note that the `%` characters have been doubled, that is so that the registry key receives the variable in its unexpanded state. As the key is of type `REG_EXPAND_SZ`, that value is expanded at registry level instead.

I have added a restart command to the end, as I&#39;d recommend doing it, *or at least a logoff*, immediately after the change.

